<Author>romanygirl
<Content>What breakfast? Lovely room, brilliant location but paid a rate to include breakfast. Breakfast was a basket of fresh (very nice) rolls, coffee from a flask, or tea bags and an urn of hot water left on a shelf in the reception hallway. The kitchenette cupboards and fridge in the room were stocked with butter, orange juice, and jams (and lots of other things) all at a (moderately expensive)price listed in the room, and therefore not included. I think there is a huge difference between including breakfast and free bread rolls will be available at the reception every morning. We felt cheated as we had deliberately chosen the place because it included breakfast.Colleen Walker 
