<Author>Girlwonder in London
<Content>Very Happy With Boarding House Berlin Mitte My partner  I rented an apartment at Boarding House Mitte for a 5-day stay in Berlin this past New Year's Eve and were not disappointed. The studio was good sized wih a great view of the famous Berlin TV tower. Our thoughtful hosts surprised us with a complementary bottle of champagne and the neighborhood with its hip, edgy shops and restaurants was just what we were looking for. The only downside of the apartment was the carpet -- it was in terrible condition with several large, off-putting stains -- but otherwise, the apartment was a great launching pad for our Berlin adventure. PS, if you do stay at the Boarding House, have at least one dinner at Monsieur Vuong's around the corner. Unbelievably yummy food. 
